						<summary>

						<p>On a stone lying in a street.</p>						

						<p>Śrīraṅga I, 1577 A.D.</p>						

						<p>This is dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka 1499, Īśvara, Chaitra śu. 15, Tuesday, Lunar eclipse</hi> corresponding to <hi rend="bold">1577 A.D., April 2.</hi></p>						

						<p>It registers the grant of a piece of land in the village Niḍumukkula in Koṇḍavīḍu to the god Gōpinātha of the same village by Bontapalle Kōṇḍama-nāyaka, son of Śrīraṅga-nāyaka and grandson of Ammā-nāyaka.</p>						

						</summary>
